A collection of scripts to assist in the management of a local/remote Drupal 6 or 7 instances via Subversion

Author: Chad Kieffer, ckieffer at gmail dot com


USE

1) Remove the .default extension on drupal_info.sh

2) Edit drupal_info.sh, add local and remote path information for your Drupal instance

3) Download Drupal core/module updates to $DownloadsPath, then run one of the following


drupal_update.sh
Update Drupal core installation 

drupal_module_update.sh
Update a shared or site-specific Drupal 6/7 module locally, then remotely via SSH and SVN
